excerpt: 3,500-acre park offering wildlife, a butterfly garden & boardwalk trails through the wetlands.
detail_description: Six Mile Cypress Slough Preserve is a 3,500-acre park in Fort Myers, offering a diverse wetland habitat for wildlife enthusiasts. The area serves as a corridor for various animals such as bears and panthers, although spotting them is rare. Visitors can expect to see alligators, egrets, woodpeckers, herons, and turtles while strolling along the well-maintained boardwalk. Once heavily logged for cypress trees, the preserve was protected thanks to student activism.
name: Six Mile Cypress Slough Preserve
address: 7751 Penzance Blvd, Fort Myers, FL 33966, USA

detail_description: Located on Florida's Gulf Coast, the River District in Historic Downtown Fort Myers is a charming waterfront area that has recently undergone revitalization. This culture and history-rich neighborhood offers a walkable, riverside experience with a mix of commercial and residential spaces. The district boasts historic appeal with its brick-paved streets lined with lively bars, boutique shops, and exceptional restaurants. It is home to numerous historic structures dating back to the early 1900s.
name: River District
address: 2180 First St #510, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

excerpt: 21 acres featuring the former homes of Edison & Ford, a research lab, botanical gardens & a museum.
detail_description: The Edison & Ford Winter Estates in Fort Myers is a 21-acre property that showcases the former homes of Thomas Edison and Henry Ford, along with a research lab, botanical gardens, and a museum. The estate pays tribute to the inventive genius of these two American icons. Visitors can explore three homes, two caretaker cottages, and a laboratory containing original gadgets used by Edison. The museum displays many of his inventions as well as historic photographs and memorabilia.
name: Edison & Ford Winter Estates
address: 2350 McGregor Blvd, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

excerpt: This 105-acre sanctuary features nature trails, a natural history museum & planetarium exhibits.
detail_description: Calusa Nature Center & Planetarium is a 105-acre sanctuary in Fort Myers, offering nature trails, a natural history museum, and planetarium exhibits. Families can explore the well-labeled nature trails, visit the planetarium and museum, observe wildlife in butterfly and bird aviaries, and enjoy picnic sites. The center hosts educational activities such as live animal presentations and movies in the planetarium. Visitors can learn about native species' environments and adaptations through exhibits featuring live animals.
name: Calusa Nature Center & Planetarium
address: 3450 Ortiz Ave, Fort Myers, FL 33905, USA

excerpt: Interactive educational museum for all ages offers 60+ exhibits including a hurricane simulator.
detail_description: The IMAG History & Science Center in Fort Myers, Florida is an interactive educational museum suitable for all ages. With over 60 exhibits, visitors can explore technology, physics, weather and other science topics. The museum also features an aquarium with marine life such as stingrays and a USS Mohawk artificial reef tank. Additionally, there are touch tanks, an Animal Lab with live critters like tarantulas and pythons, and outdoor activities including feeding fish and swans in the lagoon.
name: IMAG History & Science Center
address: 2000 Cranford Ave, Fort Myers, FL 33916, USA

excerpt: Waterfront park providing trails, up-close views of manatees, an amphitheater & kayak rentals.
detail_description: Manatee Park is a waterfront park in Fort Myers that offers trails, an amphitheater, and kayak rentals. It's a great spot to see families of manatees swimming up a tributary between December and February. The park provides up-close views of these jumbo creatures and is especially popular during the cooler months. Additionally, visitors can explore the Six-Mile Cypress Slough Preserve, which features a 1.
name: Manatee Park
address: 10901 Palm Beach Blvd, Fort Myers, FL 33905, USA

excerpt: Stately home with Georgian revival architecture, offering guided tours & event rentals.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Fort Myers, Burroughs Home and Gardens is a magnificent example of Georgian Revival architecture that transports visitors back to the early 20th century. This historic estate, once home to the affluent Burroughs family on Millionaires Row, offers guided tours showcasing its antique furnishings and personal artifacts that narrate their fascinating story. Among its intriguing exhibits are photographs and a letter from Thomas Edison discussing smoking's dangers—an unexpected gem for history buffs.
name: Burroughs Home and Gardens
address: 2505 First St, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

excerpt: Storied 1917 venue for plays, musicals & more produced by a regional professional theater company.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of downtown Fort Myers, Florida Repertory Theatre is a historic gem that has been captivating audiences since its inception. Originally constructed in 1915 and seating nearly 400 guests, this vibrant venue is dedicated to making the performing arts accessible to everyone. Since opening its doors in 1998, Florida Rep has established itself as a premier regional theater company, showcasing an impressive array of plays and musicals that have garnered both national and international acclaim.
name: Florida Repertory Theatre
address: 2268 Bay St, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

detail_description: The Butterfly Estates, a non-profit organization established in 2009, is home to a stunning glass conservatory filled with various species of butterflies. This enchanting venue boasts a small waterfall and lush greens scattered throughout. Visitors can explore the grounds or visit the Nature Interpretive Center to learn about the fascinating life processes of butterflies, from egg to caterpillar to metamorphosis.
name: The Butterfly Estates
address: 1815 Fowler St, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

excerpt: Ballpark is home to Boston Red Sox spring training & amateur league baseball games.
detail_description: JetBlue Park, also known as Fenway South, is a stylish baseball park located in the area. It serves as the spring training grounds for the Boston Red Sox team and hosts amateur league baseball games. The park opened in 2012 and features many characteristics inspired by Boston's Fenway Park, including a replica Green Monster seating area and a manual scoreboard. Visitors can experience the excitement of watching the Red Sox train and scrimmage during spring training in March.
name: JetBlue Park
address: 11500 Fenway South Drive, Fort Myers, FL 33913, USA

excerpt: Musicals, symphonies & other events are featured at this Florida SouthWestern State College performing arts hall.
detail_description: Nestled within the vibrant campus of Florida Southwestern State College, the Barbara B. Mann Performing Arts Hall stands as a beacon for culture and entertainment in the region. Named after the esteemed Barbara B. Mann, a dedicated advocate for the arts, this venue is renowned for its impressive proscenium stage—the largest in Southwest Florida.
name: Barbara B. Mann Performing Arts Hall at FSW
address: 13350 FSW Pkwy, Fort Myers, FL 33919, USA

detail_description: Fleamasters Fleamarket in Fort Myers is a massive bargain hunter's paradise, spanning over 400,000 square feet with more than 900 vendors offering an incredible variety of goods. From fresh produce to art, electric bikes to antiques, and local wines to sundresses, there's something for everyone. The market also features delightful restaurants and live entertainment for a full day of enjoyment. This lively and festive market immerses visitors in the local culture while providing an exciting shopping experience.
name: Fleamasters Fleamarket
address: 4135 Dr Martin Luther King Jr Blvd, Fort Myers, FL 33916, USA

excerpt: Family-friendly complex with a retail shop, steak-&-seafood eatery, nature park & rides for kids.
detail_description: The Shell Factory and Nature Park is a family-friendly complex located in North Tamiami Trail. It offers a diverse range of attractions, including a retail shop with sea shell collectibles, jewelry, and tropical wear. The complex also features a steak-and-seafood eatery, museums, go-karts, paddle boats, petting farm, zip line, and entertainment for children. Visitors can explore the wild animal display showcasing over 66 different animals and enjoy the largest year-round Christmas holiday shop.
name: The Shell Factory and Nature Park
address: 16554 North Cleveland Avenue, 41 N Tamiami Trl US, North Fort Myers, FL 33903, USA

excerpt: Local beer maker featuring guided tours, plus a tasting room with outdoor seating & food trucks.
detail_description: Fort Myers Brewing Company is a local gem tucked away in an industrial park, offering guided tours and a tasting room with outdoor seating. With over 20 taps, this award-winning brewery provides a laid-back atmosphere where visitors can enjoy oversized games and watch sports on TV. The dog-friendly beer garden hosts live music four nights a week and features rotating food trucks, making it the perfect spot for community gatherings.
name: Fort Myers Brewing Company
address: 12811 Commerce Lakes Dr #28, Fort Myers, FL 33913, USA

detail_description: Hammond Stadium is a popular destination for baseball enthusiasts, offering top-notch facilities and an exciting atmosphere for players and spectators alike. The stadium hosts the Minnesota Twins' spring training games, providing an opportunity for fans to catch pre-season action from February to March. Renowned for its recent multi-million dollar renovation, the park features the bullpen picnic pavilion where fans can interact with their favorite players and capture memorable moments.
name: Hammond Stadium
address: 14100 6 Mile Cypress Pkwy, Fort Myers, FL 33912, USA

excerpt: Wetland preserve featuring a walking trail, a visitor center & seasonal kayak rentals.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Cape Coral, the Four Mile Cove Ecological Preserve spans an impressive 356 acres of lush wetlands and mangrove forests. This serene haven is a paradise for nature enthusiasts, offering a scenic 1.2-mile boardwalk that meanders through diverse habitats teeming with wildlife. Bird watchers will delight in spotting eagles, herons, and various migratory species as they traverse the well-maintained trails.
name: Four Mile Cove Ecological Preserve
address: 2500 SE 24th St, Cape Coral, FL 33990, USA

detail_description: Harlem Lakes Park, located in Fort Myers, is a sprawling 279-acre recreational haven offering a wide range of outdoor activities. It features scenic walking and biking trails that meander through lush landscapes, as well as a spacious playground and charming picnic areas ideal for leisurely outings. The park also includes well-maintained basketball courts and ample seating for spectators. With its clean facilities and serene atmosphere, Harlem Lakes Park provides an enjoyable experience for visitors of all ages.
name: Harlem Lakes Park
address: 2108 Hale Ct, Fort Myers, FL 33916, USA

excerpt: Upmarket hotel with terrace dining, a top-floor bar & river views, plus an outdoor pool.
detail_description: Luminary Hotel & Co., Autograph Collection is an upscale hotel located in Fort Myers River District, offering terrace dining with river views, a top-floor bar, and an outdoor pool. The hotel is conveniently close to Harborside Event Center and Art of the Olympians Museum. Guests can enjoy various amenities such as a health club, complimentary wireless internet access, and concierge services. With three restaurants and a coffee shop on-site, guests have plenty of dining options.
name: Luminary Hotel & Co., Autograph Collection
address: 2200 Edwards Dr, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

excerpt: Relaxed hotel featuring a restaurant, a bar & a heated outdoor pool, plus a gym.
detail_description: Holiday Inn Fort Myers - Downtown Area, an IHG Hotel is a laid-back accommodation with a restaurant, bar, heated outdoor pool, and gym. It's conveniently located near the fascinating Edison and Ford Winter Estates. The hotel staff are friendly and helpful, ensuring a pleasant stay for guests. While there's no free breakfast, the nearby Dunkin Donuts offers convenience. For those attending events like weddings in the area, this hotel provides spacious rooms and excellent amenities.
name: Holiday Inn Fort Myers - Downtown Area by IHG
address: 2431 Cleveland Ave, Fort Myers, FL 33901, USA

detail_description: The Bob Rauschenberg Gallery offers a creative and thought-provoking exhibit called "He's a Mr. Know-It-All" by Wayne White, which stimulates three-dimensional thinking and mind-bending experiences. The gallery showcases an impressive all-cardboard puppet resembling Bob Rauschenberg himself, representing the high caliber of art displayed in his name.
name: Bob Rauschenberg Gallery
address: Florida Southwestern State College 8099, College Pkwy Bldg. L, Fort Myers, FL 33919, USA
